This paper deals with Bayesian network structure learning, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses probability theory and information theory, which are relevant to the sub-categories of cs.IT and cs.DM. Additionally, the paper's focus on consistency and regularity in Bayesian network structure learning may fall under the sub-category of cs.SI (social and information networks).
